The paper discusses software product lines and feature interactions, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of model-checking technology suggests a focus on logic and verification (cs.LO), while the use of variability encoding is related to formal methods and formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the application of the technique to an e-mail system suggests a possible connection to emerging technologies (cs.ET).
